File: src/builtins/set-union.tq
Symbol: transitioning javascript builtin SetPrototypeUnion(js-implicit context: NativeContext, receiver: JSAny)(other: JSAny): JSSet
Synopsis: Implements TC39 Set.prototype.union. Fast-paths for other being JSSet or JSMap with no custom iteration; SlowPath uses GetKeysIterator, IteratorStep, IteratorValue. Uses GetSetRecord, NewStableBackingTableWitness, NewUnmodifiedOrderedHashSetIterator/NewUnmodifiedOrderedHashMapIterator, CloneFixedArray, AddToSetTable, and constructs new JSSet with table=resultSetData.
Key lines: starts at builtins/set-union.tq; contains methodName constant and fastIteratorResultMap usage.
explanation: This entry indexes the Torque builtin implementing Set.prototype.union. It is a primary entry point for control/data-flow analysis of union semantics: where it clones backing table, iterates other collection, calls AddToSetTable and iterator helpers.
